27, 'In politics nothing is contemptible.', 1827, 0), (481328, 'Finality is not the language of politics.', 1827, 0), (481329, 'I think, in politics, half the people are gonna like you, and half the people are not gonna like you, no matter what you do or what you say... It''s like there are no right answers. If there were, everyone would choose the right answers. They''re all opinions.', 66949, 0), (481330, 'Revolution, n. In politics, an abrupt change in the form of misgovernment.', 224, 0), (481331, 'Alliance - in international politics, the union of two thieves who have their hands so deeply inserted in each other''s pockets that they cannot separately plunder a third.', 224, 0), (481332, 'Politics - I still think it''s a bunch of liars and a bunch of self-interest. It''s not about the people: it''s about themselves and their rise to power. They are voting on things based on whether they will have the support of the people when they vote next time. They don''t have the balls to say, ''I believe in this. I don''t care what happens.''', 8650, 0), (481333, 'I never saw anything funnier than Texas politics.', 2253, 0), (481334, 'Adroit geo-strategists take new realities into account as they try to imagine how global politics will unfold. In the foreign policy business, however, inertia is a powerful force and ''adroit'' a little-known concept.', 67849, 0), (481335, 'Politics is a herd mentality. Politicians don''t really lead. Politicians reflect what they think is consensus opinion.', 68241, 0), (481336, 'Whenever men take the law into their own hands, the loser is the law. And when the law loses, freedom languishes.', 60667, 0), (481337, 'Enter politics, and you enter the glass house; there are no secrets and no places to hide.', 36805, 0), (481338, 'When politics is no longer a mission but a profession, politicians become more self-serving than public servants.', 68911, 0), (481339, 'I think people involved in politics make good actors. Acting and politics both in