y opposed to it, and frankly, my politics don''t necessarily work for the primaries of either of our parties.', 68916, 0), (481350, 'Jesus is the politics of the new age He is about the establishment of a kingdom He is the one who has created a new time that gives us the time not only to care for the poor but to be poor. Jesus is the one who makes it possible to be nonviolent in a violent world.', 17884, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (481351, 'Politics is perhaps the only profession for which no preparation is thought necessary.', 449, 0), (481352, 'To those who have exhausted politics, nothing remains but abstract thought.', 143, 0), (481353, 'If China''s expansion into Africa and Russia''s into Latin America and the former Soviet Union are any indication, Silicon Valley''s ability to expand globally will be severely limited, if only because Beijing and Moscow have no qualms about blending politics and business.', 38015, 0), (481354, 'Politics, after all, is largely about power. And power goes to the core of our issues of control and narcissism and need to be right and tendency to divide the human race into ''us'' vs. ''them.''', 4328, 0), (481355, 'Humility is of central importance I think it''s an underappreciated virtue in the contemporary discussion of law and politics.', 67833, 0), (481356, 'Politics is about the participation and engagement of the wider citizenry - to miss that point would doom us to irrelevance.', 67458, 0), (481357, 'As Assistant Secretary of the Department of Veterans Affairs, a constant concern for me is having our veterans dragged into partisan politics.', 70540, 0), (481358, 'You can''t write about history without writing about politics at some point. History is about movements of people. ''What is criminality and what is government'' is a theme that runs through every history.', 2221, 0), (481359, 'Normally, I stay away from politics - unless I''m going to run for president.', 66917, 0), (481360, 'If you''re sort of interested in politics but sort of upset about contemporary politics, it''s kind of wonderful to read about periods who were very eloquent and admirable - generally. People are articulating ideas you can sympathize with or understand both sides of. Or at least feel like one side is saying the right things.', 69346, 0), (481361, 'One thing that education can do is it can provide us with an opportunity to understand one another better, and so while I''ve spent a lot of my time in the world of politics, I''ve always felt that it is really not politics that will solve this for us.', 25026, 0), (481362, 'I didn''t run for student council president. I don''t see myself in any way in elected office. I love policy. I''m not particularly fond of politics.', 25026, 0), (481363, 'A conservative is a man who just sits and thinks, mostly sits.', 1970, 0), (481364, 'When you read about the real history of where feminism comes from, it came from a very political point of view. I don''t believe in bringing any politics to an idea like feminism. I love the idea that women should be celebrated, but I also believe men should be, too. We need both - yin and yang.', 66719, 0), (481365, 'Look, the center right coalition in American politics today is best understood as a coalition of groups and individuals that on the issue that brings them to politics what they want from the government is to be left alone.', 72784, 0), (481366, 'While everyone else is thinking about economics and politics, executive salaries and the future of the euro, do the opposite, even if it''s hard. Invest in the spirit.', 4059, 0), (481367, 'The world we build tomorrow is born in the stories we tell our children today. Politics moves the pieces. Education changes the game.', 4059, 0), (481368, 'The only security men can have for their political liberty, consists in keeping their money in their own pockets.', 2815, 0), (481369, '''Air'' is what the world looks like: An inconvenient mashup of human politics and divine geography. We leave bits and pieces of ourselves and our history in every place we encounter.', 2700, 0), (481370, 'I was in elective politics for 24 years. I''ve made four national races, two for President, two for Vice President. I have found there are other ways to serve, and I''m enjoying them.', 13473, 0), (481371, 'There''s lots about politics I don''t feel comfortable with. To talk abou