 0), (481397, 'My hope is that 10 years from now, after I''ve been across the street at work for a while, they''ll all be glad they gave me that wonderful vote.', 10500, 0), (481398, 'It is a measure of the framers'' fear that a passing majority might find it expedient to compromise 4th Amendment values that these values were embodied in the Constitution itself.', 10500, 0), (481399, 'I know many writers who first dictate passages, then polish what they have dictated. I speak, then I polish - occasionally I do windows.', 67486, 0), (481400, 'If you don''t like the President, it costs you 90 bucks to fly to Washington to picket. If you don''t like the governor, it costs you 60 bucks to fly to Albany to picket. If you don''t like me - 90 cents.', 67486, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (481401, 'There is a danger of Scottish politics being between two sets of dinosaurs... the Nationalists who can''t accept they were rejected by the people, and some colleagues at Westminster who think nothing has changed.', 70265, 0), (481402, 'I don''t think politics has anything to do with left, right, or center. It has to do with trying to do right by people.', 43395, 0), (481403, 'A politics that is not sensitive to the concerns and circumstances of people''s lives, a politics that does not speak to and include people, is an intellectually arrogant politics that deserves to fail.', 43395, 0), (481404, 'All art is political in the sense that it serves someone''s politics.', 12152, 0), (481405, 'I am a profound pessimist both about life and about human relations and about politics and ecology. Humans are inadequate and stupid creatures who sooner or later make a mess, and those who are trying to do good do a lot more damage than those who are muddling along.', 3276, 0), (481406, 'Honestly, I''m interested in politics; I''m interested in giving back in some form, performing some sort of civic duty. But I''m not exploring a run for governor or senator or anything along those lines. I''m focused on running Disney.', 30642, 0), (481407, 'I never have been involved in politics.', 710, 0), (481408, 'In politics, readily dismissing inconvenient people can easily extend to dismissing inconvenient truths about them.', 11720, 0), (481409, 'I''ve been offered political shows before, and I don''t know anything about politics and I feel uncomfortable making political opinions - there''s consequences to them. I often think I''m wrong, so I really don''t like getting in political or religious discussions because of the giant possibility that I might be wrong.', 66936, 0), (481410, 'My passion for ideas is not matched with a passion for partisan or electoral politics.', 66144, 0), (481411, 'China''s stock market is inextricably tied to politics.', 75090, 0), (481412, 'Everything is politics.', 778, 0), (481413, 'In most places in the country, voting is looked upon as a right and a duty, but in Chicago it''s a sport.', 39403, 0), (481414, 'He too serves a certain purpose who only stands and cheers.', 2796, 0), (481415, 'Politics, as a practise, whatever its professions, has always been the systematic organization of hatreds.', 2796, 0), (481416, 'Politics... have always been the systematic organization of hatreds.', 2796, 0), (481417, 'I learnt more about politics during one South Dakota dust storm than in seven years at the university.', 15498, 0), (481418, 'I deliberately did not read anything about the Vietnam War because I felt the politics of the war eclipsed what happened to the veterans. The politics were irrelevant to what this memorial was.', 58539, 0), (481419, 'Growing up in politics I know that women decide all elections because we do all the work.', 10105, 0), (481420, 'Many politicians are in the habit of laying it down as a self-evident proposition that no people ought to be free till they are fit to use their freedom. The maxim is worthy of the fool in the old story who resolved not to go into the water till he had learned to swim.', 13860, 0), (481421, 'Of course there are regrets. I shall regret always that I found my own authentic voice in politics. I was too conservative, too conventional. Too safe, too often. Too defensive. Too reactive. Later, too often on the back foot.', 67731, 0), (481422, 'I am sure future historians will say the biggest and most astonishing change in politics has been the embracing of all the tenets of Thatcherism by the party of Keir Hardie: trade union legislation, Europe, the replacement of Trident, 10 per cent tax for people who have made millions from their companies.', 2373, 0), (481423, 'Don''t get married until you''re certain that you''re marrying the right girl. How did I know my wife was the one? I''d seen her for a couple of months. I liked her. She was a very creative person and she had a very good grip on politics and business.', 70707, 0), (481424, 'It''s true that it''s within the realm of cultural politics that young people tend to work through political issues, which I think is good, although it''s not going to solve the problems.', 61929, 0), (481425, 'The arts community is generally dominated by liberals because if you are concerned mainly with painting or sculpture, you don''t have time to study how the world works. And if you have no understanding of economics, strategy, history and politics, then naturally you would be a liberal.', 564, 0), (481426, 'First lady has been a thankless position. Eleanor Roosevelt was brilliant and had strong views. She was criticized for her politics and for her appearance. Mrs. Roosevelt was attacked for being too involved in politics. Bess Truman was criticized for being uninvolved in politics.', 68490, 0), (481427, 'When I came into politics I always thought there was a possibility I would be killed.', 10828, 0), (481428, 'Justice, sir, is the great interest of man on earth. It is the ligament which holds civilized beings and civilized nations together.', 3308, 0), (481429, 'I want to stay away from politics, or else I''ll probably end up putting my size fifteen foot into my mouth.', 68500, 0), (481430, 'I would prefer not to be involved in party politics.', 2935, 0), (481431, 'Unfortunately the global warming hysteria, as I see it, is driven by politics more than by science.', 11410, 0), (481432, '''The Means'' is about power. I have access to political insiders who helped me write a portrait of the real day-to-day in politics, which turned out to be crazier than Wall Street.', 59480, 0), (481433, 'Politics is a game and a profession. It doesn''t really serve the people the politicians are supposed to serve.', 75011, 0), (481434, 'When they see me holding fish, they can see that I am comfortable with kings as well as with paupers.', 56084, 0), (481435, 'Few businessmen are capable of being in politics, they don''t understand the democratic process, they have neither the tolerance or the depth it takes. Democracy isn''t a business.', 5930, 0), (481436, 'Though politics is by nature divisive, surely we all can agree that foster children need stability, safety, education, opportunity - and love.', 2570, 0), (481437, 'Politics ruins the character.', 4746, 0), (481438, 'Well you know it''s dangerous in politics, because especially in the Philippines there''s a lot of killing in politics.', 14894, 0), (481439, 'Electoral politics was always an objective of the Black Panther party, so Barack Obama is a part of what we dreamed and struggled and died for.', 72922, 0), (481440, 'The military destabilised my government on politically motivated charges.', 16721, 0), (481441, 'For every talent that poverty has stimulated it has blighted a hundred.', 11471, 0), (481442, 'The world is governed by opinion.', 3573, 0), (481443, 'Politics, where fat, bald, disagreeable men, unable to be candidates themselves, teach a president how to act on a public stage.', 44710, 0), (481444, 'The only politics in this country that''s relevant to black people today is the politics of revolution... none other.', 68706, 0), (481445, 'Businessmen should not put their finger in politics, because they tend to think only of their own self-interest. But I worry about the low morale in Italian industry and the lack of government initiatives to help the poor.', 66948, 0), (481446, 'I''m a longtime believer in the old adage that sunlight is the best disinfectant, particularly in politics.', 73783, 0), (481447, 'Turn on to politics, or politics will turn on you.', 23125, 0), (481448, 'The argument of the broken window pane is the most valuable argument in modern politics.', 16347, 0), (481449, 'Their very conservatism is secondhand, and they don''t know what they are conserving.', 2472, 0), (481450, 'Fortunately, we Argentines have decided to change. We believe politics needs to be led by public servants with a vocation to give and construct.', 67680, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (481451, 'As politics is disconnected from its ethical and material moorings, it becomes easier to punish and imprison young people than to educate them.', 71521, 0), (481452, 'We are naive and moralistic women. We are human beings who find politics a blight upon the human condition. And do not know how one copes with it except through politics.', 8046, 0), (481453, 'I was supposed to be women''s lib, and now I''d exceeded it and gone over into international politics.', 8046, 0), (481454, 'So you can say whatever you want and quote me however you want about politics and make the next payday, and that''s fine because I''m making that deal with you, but just mention the movie along the way, OK?', 64622, 0), (481455, 'There was a widespread indignation in the American media. They were saying, ''How can you make a movie during an election that''s about politics? What are you doing? Are you trying to influence people''s lives?'' To which my response was, ''Well, I hope so.''', 54418, 0), (481456, 'In Washington, DC, politics dominate even the most casual conversations.', 46407, 0), (481457, 'It''s called political economy because it is has nothing to do with either politics or economy.', 9981, 0), (481458, 'I like Ronald Reagan, who didn''t play crass politics, and he just articulated and delivered on broad themes that were needed. Free markets meant free markets. Deregulation. Lower tax rates. Strong national defense. And he was credible and believable.', 73789, 0), (481459, 'The problem with modern politics is everybody is doing sound bite stuff. In my stump speech, I give 20 minutes on why I think we''re off track. And I think people do really want to engage in a serious high-level discussion on how to get the country back on track because people care about their own country.', 73789, 0), (481460, 'Party honesty is party expediency.', 18162, 0), (481461, 'Your every voter, as surely as your chief magistrate, exercises a public trust.', 18162, 0), (481462, 'This is not the time for partisan bickering. This is not the time for politics as usual. Some of us are Democrats. Some of us are Republicans. Some of us are Independents. Above all, we must be Oklahomans first.', 67329, 0), (481463, 'In politics, the people I most despise are those who have no values.', 70312, 0), (481464, 'But what I''m very interested in, whether it''s writing, whether it''s hosting a show, whether it''s cooking food, I''m just into the discussions of identity, culture and the politics of culture.', 16525, 0), (481465, 'I hate it when politics play too large part in the sport.', 70092, 0), (481466, 'The public seldom forgive twice.', 23209, 0), (481467, 'What politicians want to create is irreversible change because when you leave office someone changes it back again.', 71109, 0), (481468, 'Politics is not a game for naive thinkers. You may go in as an idealist, but you certainly won''t come out as one.', 68572, 0), (481469, 'One''s politics are part of one even when one is writing. But if I want to say anything about the state of civil society, I will write an essay. The responsibilities you feel as a novelist are literary ones, I think, not civic ones. And I think politicians are interesting to write about.', 5480, 0), (481470, 'I have no child to inherit my properties. You, the people, are my only family, and to make you happy is the reason I do politics.', 73744, 0), (481471, 'Remain close to government and away from politics. It means deal more with the authorities. And less with individuals.', 75091, 0), (481472, 'In politics, madame, you need two things: friends, but above all an enemy.', 75092, 0), (481473, 'Beware the politically obsessed. They are often bright and interesting, but they have something missing in their natures; there is a hole, an empty place, and they use politics to fill it up. It leaves them somehow misshapen.', 17507, 0), (481474, 'To an intellectual who is adrift in politics, a theory is an aim; to a true politician his theory is a boundary.', 18296, 0), (481475, 'In a world where global politics is no longer a zero-sum game, it is - or should be - counterintuitive to pursue one''s interests without considering the interests of others.', 67674, 0), (481476, 'I can''t let important policy decisions hinge on the fact that an election is coming up every 90 days.', 75093, 0), (481477, 'Although he''s regularly asked to do so, God does not take sides in American politics.', 70325, 0), (481478, 'Even with politics, stuff comes around again. Woody Guthrie would recognize America today.', 52019, 0), (481479, 'From where many of us in the U.K. sit, American politics is hopelessly polarized. All kinds of issues get bundled up into two great heaps. The rest of the world, today and across the centuries, simply doesn''t see things in this horribly oversimplified way.', 4251, 0), (481480, 'Freedom of the press is guaranteed only to those who own one.', 9753, 0), (481481, 'The Vice-Presidency is sort of like the last cookie on the plate. Everybody insists he won''t take it, but somebody always does.', 5968, 0), (481482, 'I was a woman in a man''s world. I was a Democrat in a Republican administration. I was an intellectual in a world of bureaucrats. I talked differently. This may have made me a bit like an ink blot.', 3797, 0), (481483, 'The Tea Party represents stakeholders in the American system; people who were never involved in politics or thought they had to be, yet realized that political corruption and incompetence threatened not only their families, but the future of the nation itself.', 67803, 0), (481484, 'I hope that in my books there''s an undertone of politics, basic tenets of how we should live.', 686, 0), (481485, 'I know my limitations, and I don''t like politics. I was only involved because of my husband.', 67376, 0), (481486, 'Macroeconomic policy can never be devoid of politics: it involves fundamental trade-offs and affects different groups differently.', 72324, 0), (481487, 'Politics is compromise.', 68875, 0), (481488, 'Satire is fascinating stuff. It''s deadly serious, and when politics begin to break down, there is a drift towards satire, because it''s the only thing that makes any sense.', 72394, 0), (481489, 'You better take advantage of the good cigars. You don''t get much else in that job.', 72021, 0), (481490, 'And after I make a lot of money, I''ll be able to afford running for office.', 75094, 0), (481491, 'My life experiences have helped me to be less fearful. In politics, that has allowed me to take on issues sooner rather than later.', 72885, 0), (481492, 'A conservative is one who admires radicals centuries after they''re dead.', 1898, 0), (481493, 'We''re seeing quite a lot of people who really would like a return to class-based politics.', 75095, 0), (481494, 'In politics, guts is all.', 63044, 0), (481495, 'It is very creditable when a woman gets into politics. She does this at the expense of responsibilities toward her home and family and should be lauded for this.', 75096, 0), (481496, 'It is money, money, money! Not ideas, not principles, but money that reigns supreme in American politics.', 72250, 0), (481497, 'I think sometimes women are not driven by the same, albeit, testosterone power thing that pushes men to get into politics.', 73910, 0), (481498, 'You cannot spend your way out of recession or borrow your way out of debt.', 45217, 0), (481499, 'People don''t get involved with local charities or politics because they think it''s hard to make a difference and the problem feels overwhelming. But I believe that if all I''ve time for this year is to write one letter to the local council, it''s still worth doing.', 1058, 0), (481500, 'My father was a businessman, but my mother was an intellectual. She cared about culture, politics, and philosophy, so I became interested in the protest aspect of Latin American art.', 69581, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (481501, 'In politics people give you what they think you deserve and deny you what they think you want.', 61019, 0), (481502, 'People want change but not too much change. Finding that balance is tricky for every politician.', 75097, 0), (481503, 'If there is a ground zero in the cultural wars, it is Missouri, a state where pro-life groups are strong and well organized and their agenda dominates local politics.', 75097, 0), (481504, 'Economics, politics, and personalities are often inseparable.', 73812, 0), (481505, 'You know they say the most dangerous person of the world is a member of the United States Congress just home from a three-day fact-finding trip.', 66587, 0), (481506, 'Frankly, I don''t mind not being President. I just mind that someone else is.', 73043, 0), (481507, 'A politician is a person with whose politics you don''t agree if you agree with him he''s a statesman.', 55270, 0), (481508, 'Be your own politics, grow your own garden, and maybe you can help out more.', 75098, 0), (481509, 'It is our experience that political leaders do not always mean the opposite of what they say.', 43480, 0), (481510, 'Half a century ago, Ronald Reagan, the man whose relentless optimism inspired me to enter politics, famously said that he didn''t leave the Democratic Party; the party left him. I can certainly relate. I didn''t leave the Republican Party; it left me.', 75099, 0), (481511, 'In politics the choice is constantly between two evils.', 42838, 0), (481512, 'Our party is a diverse one, as is my home state of Illinois.', 74234, 0), (481513, 'If American politics are too dirty for women to take part in, there''s something wrong with American politics.', 9616, 0), (481514, 'I have an aim - I have a clear aim in my mind, and the aim is that I do not like what I see in Indian politics; it is something that is inside my heart.', 75080, 0), (481515, 'I was looking for a new challenge and got an interest in trying to make a difference for families. You become more aware of how important families are. They are the key institution in our culture. The reason I got into politics was to try to make a difference for that key institution, whether it was tax policy, education policy, or whatever.', 70552, 0), (481516, 'Confronted with the choice, the American people would choose the policeman''s truncheon over the anarchist''s bomb.', 72101, 0), (481517, 'I always voted at my party''s call, and I never thought of thinking for myself at all.', 70863, 0), (481518, 'Before I had decided to get into politics, I was laying the groundwork to have a career in the law, but that was really to lay the foundation to teach, either at the college level or law school level after my federal clerkships.', 75100, 0), (481519, 'A purely objective viewpoint does not exist in the cosmos or in politics.', 75101, 0), (481520, 'Social history might be defined negatively as the history of a people with the politics left out.', 55680, 0), (481521, 'After much prayerful consideration, I feel that I must say I have climbed my last political mountain.', 50687, 0), (481522, 'I''ve always loved history, from my youngest memories. My father enjoyed the great stories of history, like Hereward the Wake, Robin Hood, and Richard the Lionheart, and he shared them with me. I went on to do a degree in history, though I found it rather dry, because it was mostly about politics rather than dashing individuals!', 35818, 0), (481523, 'The Israelis are very smart about politics and strategy, but there are a few exceptions. One is Lebanon, the other is Gaza, where they were completely inept.', 75102, 0), (481524, 'There''s an old rule of thumb in politics that 90 percent of all 90 year-olds vote and 25 percent of all 25 year-olds vote.', 67606, 0), (481525, 'We have to ask ourselves why younger women don''t feel the need to be right up front with their politics. Is that going to set us back or is that itself a sign of progress? I don''t know the answer.', 75103, 0), (481526, 'Let''s clean up the Senate and return to politics of common ground.', 59294, 0), (481527, 'I know politics and politicians are hated, but I still believe in goodness of a heart that has selfless intentions. With the grace of God, I will make a difference.', 75104, 0), (481528, 'It''s a no-win situation with politics it''s always going to be stressful. I''m more into the comedy of life.', 75105, 0), (481529, 'There seem to me to be very few facts, at least ascertainable facts, in politics.', 64974, 0), (481530, 'My friend told me later he got the chicken pox. I told him I caught politics and never got over it.', 707, 0), (481531, 'I can remember when Democrats believed that it was the duty of America to fight for freedom over tyranny.', 72273, 0), (481532, 'A healthy democracy requires a decent society; it requires that we are honorable, generous, tolerant and respectful.', 75106, 0), (481533, 'One thing I have learned in my time in politics is that if one of the parties is shameless, the other party cannot afford to be spineless.', 75107, 0), (481534, 'Four years in the White House and two presidential campaigns is an awful long time. In politics, every year in the White House is like dog years, six years off your life.', 58816, 0), (481535, 'Politics disappears it vanishes. What remains constant is human life. So I try to develop a perspective in my writing where politics is just one of the pieces of furniture in this furnished world. It is not the purpose. It is not the goal.', 54692, 0), (481536, 'The essential ingredient of politics is timing.', 17477, 0), (481537, 'What is politics but persuading the public to vote for this and support that and endure these for the promise of those?', 13906, 0), (481538, 'I''d like to be for cinema what Shakespeare was for theatre, Marx for politics and Freud for psychology: someone after whom nothing is as it used to be.', 7312, 0), (481539, 'I can''t afford to be indifferent to politics, but I don''t have personal ambitions.', 75108, 0), (481540, 'I wasn''t a particularly brilliant student, but on the other hand, I was very active in Student Union affairs and in student politics.', 32374, 0), (481541, 'I have a temperament that doesn''t adapt well to politics. It''s because I speak my mind so much.', 72522, 0), (481542, 'I have way too shady a background to get into politics. I was a crazy kid - I was in bands, and I don''t think I''d get very far before people started digging up stuff I didn''t want them to see.', 75109, 0), (481543, 'Television is democracy at its ugliest.', 42558, 0), (481544, 'We in the Middle East like to talk politics, we like to argue. Just look at the three prophets - Moses, Jesus and Mohammad. They are all from this small region which creates problems all the time.', 75110, 0), (481545, 'The great disadvantage of our present electoral system is that it freezes the pattern of politics, and holds together the incompatible because everyone assumes that if a party splits it will be electorally slaughtered.', 75111, 0), (481546, 'Reiterating the belief that HIV is the cause of AIDS is an easy thing to do. Understanding the science and politics of the situation is much more complicated and requires study with a critical and open mind.', 75112, 0), (481547, 'Korea can''t become a ''first-class'' nation unless regulation and ''a sense of power'' disappear. The nation''s politics is the fourth-class, bureaucratic are the third-class, and business is the second-class.', 75113, 0), (481548, 'My character and my behavior is not for politics. I say what I think. I''m too liberal.', 75114, 0), (481549, 'There is a type of snobbish, pompous journalist who thinks that the only news that has any validity is war, famine, pestilence or politics. I don''t come from that school.', 75115, 0), (481550, 'If a politician murders his mother, the first response of the press or of his opponents will likely be not that it was a terrible thing to do, but rather that in a statement made six years before he had gone on record as being opposed to matricide.', 65668, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (481551, 'I think Syria is in a particularly sensitive geopolitical position in terms of the politics of the Middle East.', 75116, 0), (481552, 'There are no true friends in politics. We are all sharks circling, and waiting, for traces of blood to appear in the water.', 6083, 0), (481553, 'So begins a question which has of late become more and more urgent: what is the relation of aesthetics to politics?', 75117, 0), (481554, 'Some of the FDA''s own scientists have charged that politics, not science, is behind the FDA''s actions.', 75118, 0), (481555, 'I''m a wise Latina woman. Whatever, man. Thank God I''m not in politics, because the fact that you have to explain everything - I''d kill myself. I can''t take all those little things they dissect. I''m like, ''Oh my God, get a life.'' I don''t have time for this.', 75119, 0), (481556, 'I never let politics get personal. You can have the most intense, heated debate on issues, and so long as you keep it on issues, you can go out and have coffee afterwards and you''re good friends.', 75120, 0), (481557, 'It was through the private world of family that the public world of politics came alive for me: living in intimate proximity with people for whom larger questions of ideology and belief, as well as issues relating to politics and governance, were vivid daily realities.', 75121, 0), (481558, 'A politician will do anything to keep his job - even become a patriot.', 75122, 0), (481559, 'I had no intention of entering politics, but then the force of events led me to become involved in politics.', 75123, 0), (481560, 'Talk politics, talk about study and talk positively.', 70922, 0), (481561, 'Politics is the science of who gets what, when, and why.', 65169, 0), (481562, 'A liberal is a man who is willing to spend somebody else''s money.', 64517, 0), (481563, 'In politics it is necessary to take nothing tragically and everything seriously.', 75124, 0), (481564, 'Crime does not pay as well as politics.', 75125, 0), (481565, 'The gun is not out of Irish politics.', 75126, 0), (481566, 'The greatest gift of life is friendship, and I have received it.', 15498, 0), (481567, 'One of the most beautiful qualities of true friendship is to understand and to be understood.', 65434, 0), (481568, 'Share your smile with the world. It''s a symbol of friendship and peace.', 63466, 0), (481569, 'Walking with a friend in the dark is better than walking alone in the light.', 701, 0), (481570, 'There is nothing on this earth more to be prized than true friendship.', 1539, 0), (481571, 'Remember that the most valuable antiques are dear old friends.', 63634, 0), (481572, 'The strong bond of friendship is not always a balanced equation; friendship is not always about giving and taking in equal shares. Instead, friendship is grounded in a feeling that you know exactly who will be there for you when you need something, no matter what or when.', 19485, 0), (481573, 'I cannot even imagine where I would be today were it not for that handful of friends who have given me a heart full of joy. Let''s face it, friends make life a lot more fun.', 1789, 0), (481574, 'A single rose can be my garden... a single friend, my world.', 406, 0), (481575, 'True friends stab you in the front.', 40, 0), (481576, 'Don''t walk behind me I may not lead. Don''t walk in front of me I may not follow. Just walk beside me and be my friend.', 532, 0), (481577, 'Let us be grateful to people who make us happy, they are the charming gardeners who make our souls blossom.', 450, 0), (481578, 'Friendship is the shadow of the evening, which increases with the setting sun of life.', 2843, 0), (481579, 'There are no strangers here Only friends you haven''t yet met.', 62867, 0), (481580, 'If you have one true friend you have more than your share.', 1348, 0), (481581, 'The language of friendship is not words but meanings.', 1049, 0), (481582, 'A true friend is someone who is there for you when he''d rather be anywhere else.', 56091, 0), (481583, 'Friendship... is not something you learn in school. But if you haven''t learned the meaning of friendship, you really haven''t learned anything.', 1751, 0), (481584, 'Depth of friendship does not depend on length of acquaintance.', 430, 0), (481585, 'A true friend never gets in your way unless you happen to be going down.', 5457, 0), (481586, 'I have a loyalty that runs in my bloodstream, when I lock into someone or something, you can''t get me away from it because I commit that thoroughly. That''s in friendship, that''s a deal, that''s a commitment. Don''t give me paper - I can get the same lawyer who drew it up to break it. But if you shake my hand, that''s for life.', 2216, 0), (481587, 'A true friend freely, advises justly, assists readily, adventures boldly, takes all patiently, defends courageously, and continues a friend unchangeably.', 3256, 0), (481588, 'Love is flower like Friendship is like a sheltering tree.', 1910, 0), (481589, 'Each friend represents a world in us, a world not born until they arrive, and it is only by this meeting that a new world is born.', 23, 0), (481590, 'Of all possessions a friend is the most precious.', 1863, 0), (481591, 'Love is blind friendship closes its eyes.', 11, 0), (481592, 'Friendship is one mind in two bodies.', 3003, 0), (481593, 'As iron sharpens iron, so a friend sharpens a friend.', 5046, 0), (481594, 'When I was growing up, my mother was always a friend to my siblings and me (in addition to being all the other things a mom is), and I was always grateful for that because I knew she was someone I could talk to and joke with, and argue with and that nothing would ever harm that friendship.', 34804, 0), (481595, 'I have learned that to be with those I like is enough.', 1127, 0), (481596, 'The friend who can be silent with us in a moment of despair or confusion, who can stay with us in an hour of grief and bereavement, who can tolerate not knowing... not healing, not curing... that is a friend who cares.', 19097, 0), (481597, 'A true friend is the greatest of all blessings, and that which we take the least care of all to acquire.', 154, 0), (481598, 'Friends are born, not made.', 2796, 0), (481599, 'My friends are my estate.', 91, 0), (481600, 'The bird a nest, the spider a web, man friendship.', 221, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (481601, 'There is a magnet in your heart that will attract true friends. That magnet is unselfishness, thinking of others first; when you learn to live for others, they will live for you.', 2055, 0), (481602, 'Never explain - your friends do not need it and your enemies will not believe you anyway.', 4, 0), (481603, 'Sweet is the memory of distant friends! Like the mellow rays of the departing sun, it falls tenderly, yet sadly, on the heart.', 944, 0), (481604, 'A friend is, as it were, a second self.', 1306, 0), (481605, 'True friendship ought never to conceal what it thinks.', 62829, 0), (481606, 'Lots of people want to ride with you in the limo, but what you want is someone who will take the bus with you when the limo breaks down.', 588, 0), (481607, 'True friendship is a plant of slow growth, and must undergo and withstand the shocks of adversity, before it is entitled to the appellation.', 3161, 0), (481608, 'When we honestly ask ourselves which person in our lives means the most to us, we often find that it is those who, instead of giving advice, solutions, or cures, have chosen rather to share our pain and touch our wounds with a warm and tender hand.', 19097, 0), (481609, 'But friendship is precious, not only in the shade, but in the sunshine of life, and thanks to a benevolent arrangement the greater part of life is sunshine.', 1207, 0), (481610, 'The most I can do for my friend is simply be his friend.', 1049, 0), (481611, 'A quarrel between friends, when made up, adds a new tie to friendship.', 63291, 0), (481612, 'Of all the things which wisdom provides to make us entirely happy, much the greatest is the possession of friendship.', 1839, 0), (481613, 'A woman may very well form a friendship with a man, but for this to endure, it must be assisted by a little physical antipathy.', 11, 0), (481614, 'Your friend is your needs answered.', 5542, 0), (481615, 'But friendship is the breathing rose, with sweets in every fold.', 24754, 0), (481616, 'False friendship, like the ivy, decays and ruins the walls it embraces; but true friendship gives new life and animation to the object it supports.', 72793, 0), (481617, 'Real friendship, like real poetry, is extremely rare - and precious as a pearl.', 31617, 0), (481618, 'What sweetness is left in life, if you take away friendship? Robbing life of friendship is like robbing the world of the sun. A true friend is more to be esteemed than kinsfolk.', 1306, 0), (481619, 'The love that comes from friendship is the underlying facet of a happy life.', 2202, 0), (481620, 'The friendship that can cease has never been real.', 62829, 0), (481621, 'Friendship is a sheltering tree.', 1910, 0), (481622, 'There is something in the unselfish and self-sacrificing love of a brute, which goes directly to the heart of him who has had frequent occasion to test the paltry friendship and gossamer fidelity of mere Man.', 49, 0), (481623, 'The lust and attraction are often a given in a romance novel - I want to dig into the elements of true friendship that form a foundation for a solid, gonna-last-forever romantic relationship.', 6512, 0), (481624, 'Life has no blessing like a prudent friend.', 542, 0), (481625, 'Friendship is essentially a partnership.', 1116, 0), (481626, 'Here''s a news flash: No soldier gives his life. That''s not the way it works. Most soldiers who make a conscious decision to place themselves in harm''s way do it to protect their buddies. They do it because of the bonds of friendship - and it goes so much deeper than friendship.', 72498, 0), (481627, 'I don''t need a friend who changes when I change and who nods when I nod my shadow does that much better.', 4891, 0), (481628, 'A gang is the same as a wolf pack; gang members do not use their energies in friendship with one another, for they do not know what friendship is. If they are united, it is by the common bond of a desire to attack their world.', 940, 0), (481629, 'Every friendship goes through ups and downs. Dysfunctional patterns set in external situations cause internal friction you grow apart and then bounce back together. ', 67020, 0), (481630, 'Remember that a gesture of friendship, no matter how small, is always appreciated.', 63634, 0), (481631, 'Opposition is true friendship.', 221, 0), (481632, 'The feeling of friendship is like that of being comfortably filled with roast beef; love, like being enlivened with champagne.', 2087, 0), (481633, 'Some people are willing to betray years of friendship just to get a little bit of the spotlight.', 153, 0), (481634, 'Friendship is also about liking a person for their failings, their weakness. It''s also about mutual help, not about exploitation.', 1979, 0), (481635, 'Friendship has always belonged to the core of my spiritual journey.', 19097, 0), (481636, 'A lot of times, in our culture and our society, we put romantic love somehow on a higher plane than self-love and friendship love. You can''t do that. You have to honor and really fully invest in all these different loving relationships.', 70447, 0), (481637, 'It''s the friends you can call up at 4 a.m. that matter.', 5858, 0), (481638, 'On the relationship side, if you teach people to respond actively and constructively when someone they care about has a victory, it increases love and friendship and decreases the probability of depression.', 67434, 0), (481639, 'Every friendship is different because everyone''s personality is different.', 68008, 0), (481640, 'Never do a wrong thing to make a friend or to keep one.', 1924, 0), (481641, 'Be courteous to all, but intimate with few, and let those few be well tried before you give them your confidence.', 3161, 0), (481642, 'All you need to do to be my friend is like me.', 100, 0), (481643, 'Friendship is a plant of slow growth and must undergo and withstand the shocks of adversity before it is entitled to the appellation.', 3161, 0), (481644, 'Fan the sinking flame of hilarity with the wing of friendship and pass the rosy wine.', 96, 0), (481645, 'I had three chairs in my house; one for solitude, two for friendship, three for society.', 1049, 0), (481646, 'One of the surest evidences of friendship that one individual can display to another is telling him gently of a fault. If any other can excel it, it is listening to such a disclosure with gratitude, and amending the error.', 62596, 0), (481647, 'The differences between friends cannot but reinforce their friendship.', 15795, 0), (481648, 'General benevolence, but not general friendship, made a man what he ought to be.', 24, 0), (481649, 'Peace and friendship with all mankind is our wisest policy, and I wish we may be permitted to pursue it.', 1207, 0), (481650, 'To embrace the whole world in friendship is wisdom. This wisdom is not changeable like the flowers that bloom and fade.', 4911, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (481651, 'Eros will have naked bodies Friendship naked personalities.', 26, 0), (481652, 'Some people go to priests others to poetry I to my friends.', 113, 0), (481653, 'I don''t know if I''ve ever been in a clique. The older I''ve gotten, the more I''ve realized what a true friend really is. So my friendship circle has changed a bit.', 75127, 0), (481654, 'People come in and out of our lives, and the true test of friendship is whether you can pick back up right where you left off the last time you saw each other.', 955, 0), (481655, 'No matter what message you are about to deliver somewhere, whether it is holding out a hand of friendship, or making clear that you disapprove of something, is the fact that the person sitting across the table is a human being, so the goal is to always establish common ground.', 17868, 0), (481656, 'Have you ever thought how humiliating and distressing it was to be placed upon a sphere? For friendship it is a boon never to be able to be further apart than the antipodes. But suppose that you are leaving together to go on and on it is impossible. To go beyond a certain point is to return to where you began. ', 531, 0), (481657, 'Never contract friendship with a man that is not better than thyself.', 819, 0), (481658, 'Let there be no purpose in friendship save the deepening of the spirit.', 5542, 0), (481659, 'An excellent man he has no enemies and none of his friends like him. ', 40, 0), (481660, 'Friendship and money: oil and water.', 451, 0), (481661, 'A friend should be one in whose understanding and virtue we can equally confide, and whose opinion we can value at once for its justness and its sincerity.', 65368, 0), (481662, 'The essence of true friendship is to make allowance for another''s little lapses.', 63882, 0), (481663, 'Great is the victory, but the friendship of all is greater.', 67355, 0), (481664, 'Friendship, like the immortality of the soul, is too good to be believed.', 760, 0), (481665, 'When the world is so complicated, the simple gift of friendship is within all of our hands.', 32356, 0), (481666, 'Friendship often ends in love, but love in friendship - never.', 532, 0), (481667, 'Friendship with a man is friendship with his virtue.', 3003, 0), (481668, 'Everybody understands friendship, and friendship is different than love - it''s a different kind of love. Friendship has more freedom, more latitude. You don''t expect your friend to be as you think your friend should be; you expect your friend just to love you as a friend.', 67918, 0), (481669, 'A traitor is a betrayer - one who practices injury, while professing friendship. Benedict Arnold was a traitor, solely because, while professing friendship for the American cause, he attempted to injure it. An open enemy, however criminal in other respects, is no traitor.', 2815, 0), (481670, 'I take friendship very seriously.', 6613, 0), (481671, 'Pak-China friendship is higher than Himalayas, deeper than ocean, sweeter than honey, and stronger than steel.', 67079, 0), (481672, 'The dupe of friendship, and the fool of love; have I not reason to hate and to despise myself? Indeed I do; and chiefly for not having hated and despised the world enough.', 8948, 0), (481673, 'Friends confront each other sometimes, and sometimes the friendship lasts, and sometimes it doesn''t.', 75128, 0), (481674, 'The joys of friendship inert the heart and fizzy home bouncing jubilantly with laughter-buttered love.', 75129, 0), (481675, 'One friend in a lifetime is much, two are many, three are hardly possible. Friendship needs a certain parallelism of life, a community of thought, a rivalry of aim.', 2796, 0), (481676, 'Shows like ''Sex and the City'' got women involved again in a political way. They were drawn into the personal stories of the four women who together make up one complete cosmopolitan woman. We want to have community, and the show filled that void in our lives: friendship between women.', 51377, 0), (481677, 'Love is rarer than genius itself. And friendship is rarer than love.', 9561, 0), (481678, 'The ideal friendship is to feel as one while remaining two.', 73291, 0), (481679, 'Few things tend more to alienate friendship than a want of punctuality in our engagements. I have known the breach of a promise to dine or sup to break up more than one intimacy.', 8948, 0), (481680, 'I do think, in time, people will have, sort of, relationships with certain kinds of robots - not every robot, but certain kinds of robots - where they might feel that it is a sort of friendship, but it''s going to be of a robot-human kind.', 75130, 0), (481681, 'We must reach out our hand in friendship and dignity both to those who would befriend us and those who would be our enemy.', 52297, 0), (481682, 'Friendship, like love, is destroyed by long absence, though it may be increased by short intermissions.', 2087, 0), (481683, 'I''m loyal, and I like my friends. Friendship enriches your life and makes it more interesting.', 75131, 0), (481684, 'Acquaintances we meet, enjoy, and can easily leave behind; but friendship grows deep roots.', 63634, 0), (481685, 'He who hath many friends hath none.', 1116, 0), (481686, 'Never have a companion that casts you in the shade.', 1255, 0), (481687, 'You find out who your real friends are when you''re involved in a scandal.', 1553, 0), (481688, 'It is not so much our friends'' help that helps us, as the confidence of their help.', 1839, 0), (481689, 'A man cannot be said to succeed in this life who does not satisfy one friend.', 1049, 0), (481690, 'How delightful to find a friend in everyone.', 1254, 0), (481691, 'We call that person who has lost his father, an orphan; and a widower that man who has lost his wife. But that man who has known the immense unhappiness of losing a friend, by what name do we call him? Here every language is silent and holds its peace in impotence.', 563, 0), (481692, 'Nothing but heaven itself is better 