INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (481701, 'Our way is straight and clear - the building up of a socialist democracy at home, with freedom and prosperity for all, and the maintenance of world peace and friendship with all nations abroad.', 67654, 0), (481702, 'Friendship is but another name for an alliance with the follies and the misfortunes of others. Our own share of miseries is sufficient: why enter then as volunteers into those of another?', 1207, 0), (481703, 'I love life in spite of all that mars it. I love friendship, jokes and laughter.', 31617, 0), (481704, 'Friendship is the complete explanation of what a Cheetah Girl is - if you have that true friendship, you can conquer anything you want.', 70383, 0), (481705, 'Friendship is like money, easier made than kept.', 4111, 0), (481706, 'If we would build on a sure foundation in friendship, we must love friends for their sake rather than for our own.', 42, 0), (481707, 'Don''t flatter yourselves that friendship authorizes you to say disagreeable things to your intimates. On the contrary, the nearer you come into relation with a person, the more necessary do tact and courtesy become.', 24754, 0), (481708, 'Secrecy is the chastity of friendship.', 3943, 0), (481709, 'The sacrifices of friendship were beautiful in her eyes as long as she was not asked to make them.', 75132, 0), (481710, 'Friendship is composed of a single soul inhabiting two bodies.', 62134, 0), (481711, 'Friendship with ones self is all important, because without it one cannot be friends with anyone else in the world.', 141, 0), (481712, 'It is difficult to obtain the friendship of a cat. It is a philosophical animal... one that does not place its affections thoughtlessly.', 4453, 0), (481713, 'Friendship is a very taxing and arduous form of leisure activity.', 69091, 0), (481714, 'Pity and friendship are two passions incompatible with each other.', 2204, 0), (481715, 'Friendship always benefits love sometimes injures.', 1379, 0), (481716, 'The beginning of a friendship, the fact that two people out of the thousands around them can meet and connect and become friends, seems like a kind of magic to me. But maintaining a friendship requires work. I don''t mean that as a bad thing. Good art requires work as well.', 1280, 0), (481717, 'Men and women can absolutely be friends, and that''s what we need to be. Part of the problem is that we aren''t friends enough. Our relationships are negotiations, and that is not friendship.', 68255, 0), (481718, 'Since the Korean War, U.S. and South Korea have established an enduring friendship with shared interests, such as denuclearizing the Korean Peninsula, combating aggression abroad and developing our economies.', 41313, 0), (481719, 'Sweat makes good friendship cement.', 65217, 0), (481720, 'To me, Green Arrow in the past, what people loved about Oliver Queen pre-New 52 was his relationships with other heroes. Like his friendship with Green Lantern, his animosity with Hawkman, his romance with Black Canary - these are all the things that sort of defined him.', 61316, 0), (481721, 'I feel friendship towards philosophers, but towards sophists, teachers of literature, or any other such kind of godforsaken people, I neither feel friendship now, nor may I ever do so in the future.', 72615, 0), (481722, 'When you think back in history about producers and artists or writers who''ve had good synergy, a lot of times they date, or they''re married, or there''s a friendship and a kinship.', 69212, 0), (481723, 'We will seek friendship and goodwill with the nations of the world - but we do so with the understanding that it is the right of all nations to put their own interests first.', 64643, 0), (481724, 'I have discovered that my interest in my dear pupil, Mabel, has ripened into a far deeper feeling than that of mere friendship. In fact, I know that I have learned to love her very sincerely.', 2018, 0), (481725, 'I think what ''The Hobbit'' and Middle-earth deal in are quite universal and timeless themes of honour and love and friendship... so they''re things that do resonate with people.', 13073, 0), (481726, 'Perfect friendship is the friendship of men who are good, and alike in excellence; for these wish well alike to each other qua good, and they are good in themselves.', 1116, 0), (481727, 'To want friendship is a great fault. Friendship ought to be a gratuitous joy, like the joys afforded by art or life.', 1662, 0), (481728, 'It''s the most exciting thing to watch God work when I''ve asked him about something, to listen to him and watch him work. It''s like this friendship, and it just grows and grows and grows and grows.', 1789, 0), (481729, 'When the bank asks me about my assets, I include my friendship with Regis Philbin.', 2081, 0), (481730, 'Where is instruction in relationships, in the management of career, in the raising of children, in the pursuit of friendship, in the wise approach to anxiety and death? All this sort of stuff I craved to learn about when I was a student and down to this day.', 639, 0), (481731, 'If you''re going through friendship issues, I would say, first of all take a step back. How important is the friendship to you? Sometimes, if someone''s not being a good friend to you and isn''t treating you the way you should be treated, then you kind of have to move on sometimes.', 16615, 0), (481732, 'The little trouble in the world that is not due to love is due to friendship.', 13154, 0), (481733, 'Loyalty and friendship trumps politics for me.', 67333, 0), (481734, 'Ultimately, it''s a sense of camaraderie and friendship with local people that is core to my journeys.', 67893, 0), (481735, 'To like and dislike the same things, this is what makes a solid friendship.', 4812, 0), (481736, 'I cherish the memory of being a friend of Frank Sinatra on a friendship level to the point where we really hung out. We worked in Vegas, we''d talk on the phone, and if I wasn''t doing anything, I''d fly out, and I spent time in Palm Springs at his house - on a level the way friends would be, not with a whole crowd of people.', 72064, 0), (481737, 'So far as it depends on the course of this government, our relations of good will and friendship will be sedulously cultivated with all nations.', 68667, 0), (481738, 'And though my Lord hath lost his estate and been banished out of his country, yet neither despised poverty nor pinching necessity could make him break the bonds of friendship or weaken his loyal duty.', 26393, 0), (481739, 'In closing I wish to say that while I was sorely beset by a number of white riders in my racing days, I have also enjoyed the friendship of countless thousands of white men whom I class as among my closest friends.', 71342, 0), (481740, 'To some it may be a thrill to be known, to me it''s a thrill to start a friendship even up.', 75133, 0), (481741, 'I can tell you, dearest friend, that if it became known how much friendship, love and a world of human and spiritual references I have smuggled into these three movements, the adherents of programme music - should there be any left - would go mad with joy.', 71803, 0), (481742, 'Never be afraid to meet to the hilt the demand of either work, or friendship - two of life''s major assets.', 75134, 0), (481743, 'Without wearing any mask we are conscious of, we have a special face for each friend.', 24754, 0), (481744, 'I have two or three guys that I''m really close to. We have a great friendship, and I think that helps our songwriting relationship. It''s hard to start... with new people and cover the ground that I''ve covered with those guys.', 67010, 0), (481745, 'Sustaining true friendship is a lot more challenging than we give it credit for.', 67020, 0), (481746, 'I have enjoyed most particularly reading the correspondence between Gustav Mahler and Richard Strauss. The genuine friendship, competitiveness and support that thread through their communications are life lessons for us all.', 65864, 0), (481747, 'Aristotle uses a mother''s love for her child as the prime example of love or friendship.', 69091, 0), (481748, 'I''m single, footloose and fancy free, I have no responsibilities, no anchors. Work, friendship and self-improvement, that''s me.', 67004, 0), (481749, 'I keep my friends as misers do their treasure, because, of all the things granted us by wisdom, none is greater or better than friendship.', 62366, 0), (481750, 'I''ve learned from my dealings with Johnny Carson that no matter what kind of friendship you think you have with people you''re working with, when the chips are down, it''s all about business.', 17330, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (481751, 'An insincere and evil friend is more to be feared than a wild beast; a wild beast may wound your body, but an evil friend will wound your mind.', 1471, 0), (481752, 'Friendship is a wildly underrated medication.', 21122, 0), (481753, 'There is no friendship in trade.', 72941, 0), (481754, 'Love demands infinitely less than friendship.', 6546, 0), (481755, 'Came but for friendship, and took away love.', 790, 0), (481756, 'Suspicion is the cancer of friendship.', 66050, 0), (481757, 'We became friends as we became a band. Our friendship evolved as the band evolved. It had its ups and downs, but it was mostly ups for the four of us. We got along well almost all of the time. Hey! We liked each other and we still do.', 75135, 0), (481758, 'All love that has not friendship for its base, is like a mansion built upon the sand.', 541, 0), (481759, 'I''ve always wanted to be a mom because I want to give a kid all of the magical gifts my mom gave to me, such as love and friendship. She and I had this incredible connection that was so unbelievable.', 2549, 0), (481760, 'Loyalty and friendship, which is to me the same, created all the wealth that I''ve ever thought I''d have.', 66774, 0), (481761, 'Men kick friendship around like a football, but it doesn''t seem to crack. Women treat it like glass and it goes to pieces.', 1407, 0), (481762, 'He has no enemies, but is intensely disliked by his friends.', 40, 0), (481763, 'Friendship, of itself a holy tie, is made more sacred by adversity.', 432, 0), (481764, 'Show me a genuine case of platonic friendship, and I shall show you two old or homely faces.', 36106, 0), (481765, 'China has been committed to the independent foreign policy of peace and has developed friendship and cooperation with all countries on the basis of the Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence.', 75136, 0), (481766, 'I''ve got some great guy friends. They can start out as crushes. But when you realize something isn''t going to happen, you make a choice whether or not the friendship is worth it. And it usually is. Then you can laugh about the fact that you used to have a crush on him or he had one on you.', 68409, 0), (481767, 'Friendships are the family we make - not the one we inherit. I''ve always been someone to whom friendship, elective affinities, is as important as family.', 2065, 0), (481768, 'Any friendship or relationship is about a language.', 71006, 0), (481769, 'Much of my work over the years has developed the premise that women''s styles of friendship and conversation aren''t inherently better than men''s, simply different.', 41330, 0), (481770, 'The part which American friendship played in helping us to win the freedom we enjoy in this part of Ireland has been gratefully recognized and acknowledged by our people.', 67600, 0), (481771, 'As is natural with contiguous states having like institutions and like aims of advancement and development, the friendship of the United States and Mexico has been constantly maintained.', 66663, 0), (481772, 'When two people first meet, they can only have a very ordinary kind of friendship. But when you begin to understand each other, when you get close to them, you discover that you''re suddenly eager to know him or her even better.', 73806, 0), (481773, 'My aim is to create a happy society with genuine friendship. Friendship between Tibetan and Chinese peoples is very essential.', 5025, 0), (481774, 'Our friends interpret the world and ourselves to us, if we take them tenderly and truly.', 13866, 0), (481775, 'Many a friendship, long, loyal, and self-sacrificing, rested at first on no thicker a foundation than a kind word.', 27036, 0), (481776, 'One''s friends are that part of the human race with which one can be human.', 2683, 0), (481777, 'Silences make the real conversations between friends. Not the saying but the never needing to say is what counts.', 5899, 0), (481778, 'It is important to our friends to believe that we are unreservedly frank with them, and important to friendship that we are not.', 1932, 0), (481779, 'You win the victory when you yield to friends.', 139, 0), (481780, 'The most deadly fruit is borne by the hatred which one grafts on an extinguished friendship.', 3244, 0), (481781, 'Friendship''s the wine of life: but friendship new... is neither strong nor pure.', 4028, 0), (481782, 'What I cannot love, I overlook. Is that real friendship?', 23, 0), (481783, 'Friendship is an arrangement by which we undertake to exchange small favors for big ones.', 48659, 0), (481784, 'To cement a new friendship, especially between foreigners or persons of a different social world, a spark with which both were secretly charged must fly from person to person, and cut across the accidents of place and time.', 18147, 0), (481785, 'Conjugal love, or the friendship of spouses, can persist even after sexual desires have weakened, withered, and disappeared.', 69091, 0), (481786, 'Although the troops have struck us, we throw it all behind and are glad to meet you in peace and friendship.', 68770, 0), (481787, 'Working with people, the musical part is one thing but the personal part is totally different and just as critical. If the friendship is there and it''s a lasting friendship, then it will take care of itself.', 75137, 0), (481788, 'Caring for but never trying to own may be a further way to define friendship.', 11428, 0), (481789, 'Time makes friendship stronger, but love weaker.', 5879, 0), (481790, 'There are no rules for friendship. It must be left to itself. We cannot force it any more than love.', 8948, 0), (481791, 'Friendship without self-interest is one of the rare and beautiful things of life.', 62523, 0), (481792, 'The friendship we share grows amidst the craggy rock pond reeds of water spray fireflies scented with bonfires.', 75129, 0), (481793, 'Plunderous is the palate I gift to you, openly I hug the universe of our friendship expanding its outer limit.'